      "slideNumber": 17,
      "title": "Russian peasant Multiplication",
      "content": [
        "Algorithm for multiplying two positive integers called multiplication `a la russe or the Russian peasant method. Which is also divided by a constant factor",
        "Let n and m be positive integers whose product we want to compute, and let us measure the instance size by the value of n.",
        "if n is even, an instance of half the size has to deal with n/2",
        "we have an obvious formula relating the solution to the problem’s larger instance to the solution to the smaller one  (n . m = n/2 . 2m)",
        "For odd numbers ( n . m= n−1/ 2 . 2m +m)."
      ],
      "ocrContent": "",
      "notes": "",
      "images": [],
      "isTextLight": false,
